						<summary>

						<p>Four detached stones built into the platform round the flag-staff in front of the same temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājakēsarivarmaṉ</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Śrī-Rājarājadēva (I): Date lost: (accn.) 985 A.D. 11th century.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is very much damaged. It contains part of the <hi rend="italic">praśasti</hi> of the king. It appears to record the remission of tax on some land belonging to a certain Rājarājaśanman by the <hi rend="italic">sabhai</hi> (assembly) of Śrī-Vīranārāyaṇachchaturvēdimaṅgalam, a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēya i</hi>n Rājēndraśiṅga-vaḷaṅāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
